<entry>
<form>tavaḷai<c type="geminated">p</c> pāyttu+</form>
<def>the principle of the frog's leap, whereby a cūttiram is so constructed as to have reference to the next but one that follows it</def>
<form type="sandhi">tavaḷai<c type="geminated">p</c>pāyttup</form>
<gramGrp>
  <gram type="role">noun</gram>
</gramGrp>
</entry>
<entry>
<form>paruntiṉ viḻukkāṭ*</form>
<def>The principle of the kite's swoop whereby a sūtra occurring in a treatise is not directly connected either with its preceding or succeeding sūtra, but connected with some remote sūtra</def>
<form type="sandhi">paruntiṉviḻukkāṭ</form>
<gramGrp>
  <gram type="role">noun</gram>
</gramGrp>
</entry>
